reviews.text: Nice and cheap local restaurant. The typical set lunch mostly around $40-$60. The set lunch comes with scramble egg with ham, noodle and drink. The scramble egg is using 3.6 Hokkaido milk, which is rather creamy and tasty. The noodle is ok and you may also add $6 for additional sausage or chicken wings. The milk tea is quite ok, it is smooth and milky. It is a nice and cheap .

Good local HK style breakfast with macaroni and instant noodles in tomato/chicken soup, with various combination such as luncheon meat, beef slice, ham etc. Also a selection of western fares such as pancakes and sussages. 

The Japanese Style omelette is quite good. Toast is thick and soft. 

The coffee and teas are quite nice.

One of the few shops that opens up early.

Not what I was expecting. I was expecting a real Hong Kong cafe, but that was my-bad for not looking thoroughly at the pictures. They do have coffee and milk teas, but not the legit Hong-Kong-kind I was searching for. 

This cafe is located in a mall on the 3rd floor? The waitress was hasty, but also efficient. She did not really want to make suggestions or had time to. Must be ready to order or she walks away to do other things. 

PROS: opened early. most establishments are still closed for breakfast around 8am.
Fast food.
Acquired taste

result.name: Silvercord

reviews.text: Well equipped mall at the center of the shopping district. Have affordable shops as supposed to all the designer brands near by. Good places to eat inside, also affordable.

Silvercord is a shopping mall and office complex at the heart of Canton Road in Tsimshatsui. Its location is very convenient with walking bridge connected to the Harbour City, the largest shopping mall in Hong Kong. However, the mall seems a bit outdated in the interior decoration and the mall design. Always use liked a stepping stone to the nearest Harbour City from my point of view.

The concierge is really friendly always smiling and super helpful, he knows what service means, he took the pain to help me and not just by pointing in a vague direction, while welcoming me, and i felt like a guest in the building rather than an annoyance!!! Keep it up management you're doing great to have such awesome staff!!
Genki Sushi is the best addition to this mall
Good quality products. Attractive.
